#tr.en: Išum is a door: before them it is barred.
27. %n īšum | daltum-ma || edil | pānu[ššu]n
#note: Compare @bib{lambert1980line@83}: “In the Erra Epic the Seven wished to be fighting, but their master Erra declined to go to battle for the moment and his vizier accordingly restrained them, not by literal incarceration, but simply by his command. Thus this line could be paraphrased: ‘Išum kept them inactive’.” On this line, see also @bib{RN714@358}.
AššNA2 i 25'. {d}i-šum dal-tum₃#-ma & e-di-il pa#-nu-uš-šu₂
