#tr.en: “Let the Igigi hear it and extol your name!
62. %n igīgū | lišmû-ma || lišarbû | šumka
NinNA3 ii 4. [x x x x x x x x x x] MU-ka
HuzNA1 i 62. {d}i₂-gi₃-gi₃ liš-mu-ma & li-šar!#(ŠIR₃)-bu & MU-[k]a

#tr.en: “Let the Anunnaki hear it and fear the mention of you!
63. %n anunnakū | lišmû-ma || lišhuṭ[ū] | zikirka
NinNA3 ii 5. [x x x x x x x x x x x s]i₃-qar-ka
AššNA2 ii 1'. [{d}]a*#-nun*#-[na-ki x x x x x x x x x]
#note: Collation of the line in Lambert’s folio 18397.
HuzNA1 i 63. {d}a-nun-na-ki liš-mu-ma & liš-hu-ṭ[u] & zi-ki[r]-ka

#tr.en: “Let the gods hear it and bend for your yoke!
64. %n ilū | lišmû-ma || liknušū | ana nīrīka
NinNA3 ii 6. [x x x x x x x x x n]i-ri-ka
AššNA2 ii 2'. DINGIR-MEŠ & [x x x x x x x x x x]
