#note: As noted by @bib{RN31@194}, the line contains an etymographical explanation of @akk{{giš}MES}, in which @akk{GIŠ} = @i{iṣu}, “tree,” and @akk{MES} = @i{eṭlu}, “lad.” The transliteration of @akk{iṣ-ṣu} as @akk{GIŠ-ṣu} (i.e., as @i{iṣu}) is defended in @bib{RN1518@194-195 fn. 517}.
