#tr.en: “Where is the pure blue pigment that was made (as) splendid (as) lapis lazuli?
154. %n ali | ebbu | zagindurû || ša ušamsakū | uqnâ
#note: Lambert @i{apud} @bib{RN31@194-195} suggests parsing the verb as @i{nasāqu}, “to choose.” Here the interpretation as @i{nasāku}, “in Ordnung bringen o.ä.” (so @bib{borger1971tempelbau@79-80}) is preferred. Although the verb could be a first person, it seems preferable to interpret it as a third person plural, either as an impersonal form, or with the gods that appear in the following lines as its subject. On @i{zagindurû} as “Egyptian blue,” see @bib{thavapalan2020meaning@355-366}, with previous bibliography. @i{uqnû}, now restored thanks to MS TarNA1, is interpreted as a predicative complement (on this category, see @bib{fromebllab0003@79-81}); compare II 34: @i{šumsukat eli ša mahri}, “I made more splendid than before.”
// cf. L I.5 SB "II" 32
